/*
Multi-Agent Research Assistant — showcase of every orchestration pattern

  ┌──────────┐  POST /api/research  ┌────────────────┐
  │ Browser  │ ───────────────────► │ Research Topic │  (coordinator)
  │  (page)  │ ◄─────────────────── │     Agent      │
  └──────────┘       report          └───────┬────────┘
                                             │
                           ┌─────────────────┼──────────────────┐
                           ▼                 ▼                  ▼
                    ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────┐
                    │ Research All │  │ Polished Rpt │   │  Quality     │
                    │  (for each)  │  │ (repeat      │   │   Critic     │
                    └──────┬───────┘  │  until...)   │   └──────────────┘
                           │          └──────────────┘
                           ▼
                    ┌──────────────┐
                    │  Researcher  │  (specialist — streams token-by-token)
                    └──────────────┘

AGENT FLOW:

  Research Topic [skill: Report Style]
    │
    ├─ wraps topic into a 1-item list
    │
    ├─> Research All [dynamic fan-out]
    │     │
    │     └─ for each question: call Researcher ─> append to findings
    │
    └─> Polished Report [iterative refinement]
          │
          └─ repeat until score > 7, max 2 times:
               ├─ improve the draft
               └─ call Quality Critic ─> score

Five orchestration patterns in one file:
  1. Sequential chain     — Research Topic delegates step-by-step
  2. Parallel fan-out     — Grade Answer runs two graders simultaneously
  3. Dynamic fan-out      — Research All loops a list through Researcher
  4. Iterative refinement — Polished Report loops until the critic passes
  5. Skill bundle         — Report Style shared as reusable instructions
*/

# JUMP TO: Database | Specialists | Skill | Coordinators | Endpoints | Frontend

build for web and javascript backend

database is local memory

# Database

create a Reports table:
  topic, required
  report, required
  created_at, auto

# Specialists — small, focused, each does one thing
# Streaming is default for text agents; coordinators see the final string,
# not the async generator (compiler drains it automatically).

agent 'Researcher' receives question:
  answer = ask claude 'Answer this question in 2-3 sentences' with question
  send back answer

agent 'Fact Checker' receives claim:
  verdict = ask claude 'Rate this claim 1-10 for factual accuracy. Return just the number.' with claim
  send back verdict

agent 'Sentiment Rater' receives claim:
  tone = ask claude 'Is this answer confident, cautious, or uncertain? One word.' with claim
  send back tone

agent 'Quality Critic' receives draft:
  grade = ask claude 'Rate this report 1-10 for clarity and completeness. Return just the number.' with draft
  send back grade

# Skill — reusable tool + instruction bundle merged into any agent that uses it
# `uses skills:` prepends these instructions to the agent's prompt and
# inherits any listed tools.

skill 'Report Style':
  instructions:
    Use short paragraphs.
    Lead with the answer, follow with the reasoning.
    Never say 'As an AI'.

# Coordinators

# Pattern 2 — Parallel fan-out. Known arity: exactly two graders run at
# once and meet back at the `create grade` record.
agent 'Grade Answer' receives claim:
  do these at the same time:
    accuracy = call 'Fact Checker' with claim
    tone = call 'Sentiment Rater' with claim
  create grade:
    accuracy is accuracy
    tone is tone
  send back grade

# Pattern 3 — Dynamic fan-out. Runtime-sized list of questions, each
# delegated to a specialist, results accumulated into a list.
agent 'Research All' receives questions:
  findings is an empty list
  for each question in questions:
    answer = call 'Researcher' with question
    add answer to findings
  send back findings

# Pattern 4 — Iterative refinement. Loops the draft through a critic
# until the quality bar is met, or stops after the max cap. The cap
# keeps the loop bounded when the agent plateaus below the bar.
agent 'Polished Report' receives findings:
  draft = ask claude 'Synthesize these findings into a final report' with findings
  grade = 0
  repeat until grade is greater than 7, max 2 times:
    draft = ask claude 'Improve the clarity and completeness of this report' with draft
    grade = call 'Quality Critic' with draft
  send back draft

# Pattern 1 — Sequential chain. Top-level coordinator: wrap the single
# topic into a list (so Research All can loop), fan out, then refine.
agent 'Research Topic' receives topic:
  uses skills: 'Report Style'
  question_list is an empty list
  add topic to question_list
  findings = call 'Research All' with question_list
  final_report = call 'Polished Report' with findings
  send back final_report

# Endpoints

allow server to accept requests from frontend

when user sends request to /api/research:
  final_report = call 'Research Topic' with request's topic
  saved = save request as new Report with report is final_report
  send back saved

when user requests data from /api/reports:
  all_reports = get all Reports
  send back all_reports

# Frontend

page 'Multi-Agent Research':
  on page load get reports from '/api/reports'
  heading 'Research Assistant'
  text 'Enter a topic. The coordinator dispatches a specialist to research it, loops a critic to refine the final report, and shows the polished answer below.'
  'Topic' is a text input saved as a topic
  button 'Research':
    send topic as a new request to '/api/research'
    get reports from '/api/reports'
    topic is ''
  display reports as table showing topic, report, created_at
